eu.cqse.check.framework.preprocessor.c.new_c_preprocessor

Class NewCPreprocessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.preprocessor.c.new_c_preprocessor.NewCPreprocessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPreprocessor

    public class NewCPreprocessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IPreprocessor
    Main class of the C/C++ preprocessor. It iterates over the tokens of a given BasicTokenElementInfo and generates PreprocessorTokenReplacement objects for each token sequence that is replaced by a different token sequence.

    Besides the whole-file iteration, this class handles simple tasks such as #define directives. Complex tasks such as macro expansion or #if directives are delegated (e.g., to NewMacroInvocationPreprocessor and IfDirectivePreprocessor.

      • computeTopLevelReplacements

        public java.util.List<PreprocessorTokenReplacement> computeTopLevelReplacements(java.lang.String uniformPath,
                                                                                java.util.List<IToken> fileTokens)
        Computes a list of PreprocessorTokenReplacements that represent the result of preprocessing the given tokens as if they were the entire content of a C/C++ file

        This method assumes that the file that spawns a compilation unit (e.g., a xy.c file). This should not be called if the file is processed because of an include statement (#include xy.c) because we then would lose the include-hierarchy info.

        Returns:
        A list of token replacements. Each element's PreprocessorTokenReplacement.originalTokensStartIndex refers to the given fileTokens list. This list is sorted by PreprocessorTokenReplacement.originalTokensStartIndex and the replaced regions are non-overlapping.

      • getCurrentDefines

        public ParsedMacroProvider getCurrentDefines()
        Returns the macro provider used by this Preprocessor. It contains the macros that are defined at the current state of the preprocessor. The defined macros might change if this preprocessor is still or again used to process code.
